.TH RESOLVERCTL 1 "2026-03-19" "stophammer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
resolverctl \- inspect or toggle resolver queue state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B resolverctl
[
.BI --db " PATH"
]
[
.B status
|
.B import-active
|
.B import-idle
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B resolverctl
is a small operational helper for the durable resolver queue.

It can:

- print queue counts and current import pause state
- set
.BR resolver_state.import_active=true
before a large import
- clear that flag afterwards so
.BR resolverd
can resume draining the queue
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --db " PATH"
Path to the SQLite database. Defaults to
.BR ./stophammer.db .
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Prints
.BR import_active ,
.BR import_stale ,
.BR import_heartbeat_at ,
and queue total, ready, locked, and failed counts.
.TP
.B import-active
Sets
.BR resolver_state.import_active=true
and refreshes the import heartbeat timestamp.
.TP
.B import-idle
Sets
.BR resolver_state.import_active=false .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Check queue status:
.nf
cargo run --bin resolverctl -- status
.fi
.TP
Pause the queue around a bulk import:
.nf
cargo run --bin resolverctl -- import-active
# run bulk import
cargo run --bin resolverctl -- import-idle
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR resolverd (1),
.BR backfill_canonical (1),
.BR stophammer (1)
